<<<api>>>: StringTokenizer.nextToken
<<<code>>>: 
```java
String str = "12345,56789";
StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(str, ",");
Double dob1 = Double.parseDouble(st.nextToken());
Double dob2 = Double.parseDouble(st.nextToken());
```
<<<explanation>>>: The StringTokenizer class in Java is used to break a string into tokens. In this case, we are using the comma as a delimiter to split the string into two parts. The nextToken() method is used to get the next token from the string. The Double.parseDouble() method is then used to convert the string tokens into double values. The first token is stored in dob1 and the second token is stored in dob2.
